	#. What is an equation for the set of points in $#R#^3$ that are distance $3$ from the point $(2, 3, -1)$? What does this shape of this set look like? Check your answer with <a href="https://www.desmos.com/3d">Desmos 3D</a>.

	#. What is an equation for a cylinder in $#R#^3$ parallel to the $y$-axis, with radius $4$, and whose central axis contains the point $(2, 3, 1)$? Check your answer with <a href="https://www.desmos.com/3d">Desmos 3D</a>.

	- - -

	#. Let $\vec{v} = \left< 0, 3, 4 \right>$ and let $\vec{w} = \vec{i} - 2\vec{j} + \vec{k}$.

	> a) Find $\left| \left| \vec{v} \right| \right|$ and $\left| \left| \vec{w} \right| \right|$.

	> b) Sketch $\vec{v}$ and $\vec{w}$ in $#R#^3$.

	> c) Find $\vec{v} + \vec{w}$ and $2\vec{v} - \vec{w}$ in component form and sketch them both.

	> d) Find unit vectors in the same direction as $\vec{v}$ and $\vec{w}$, respectively.

	- - -

	#. The sum of the forces acting on an object is called the **net force**, and an object is said to be in static equilibrium if the net force acting on it is $\vec{0}$. Suppose the forces $F_1 = \left< 1, 4, -3 \right>$, $F_2 = \left< 0, 0, 5 \right>$, $F_3 = \left< 4, 5, 0 \right>$, and an unknown force $F_4$ are acting on an object that is in static equilibrium. Find $F_4$.

