	#. For each of the following points $q$, find all $y$-values so that the point $p = (6, y, -8)$ is exactly $5$ units away from $q$, or explain why no such $y$-values exist.

	> a) $q = (5, 1, -5)$.

	> b) $q = (2, -4, -2)$.

	> c) $q = (9, 9, -12)$.

